## Summary

Detects **SQL Injection** vulnerabilities in TypeScript (Node.js) code by tracking untrusted data flow from request inputs into SQL execution functions **without** parameterization. Pays special attention to TypeScript-specific false-sanitization patterns (`as` casts, non-null `!`, type annotations, Zod parses, type guards) and distinguishes safe tagged-template raw-SQL APIs (`$queryRaw`, `sql\`...\``) from their unsafe siblings (`$queryRawUnsafe`, `sql.raw`).
